  *NOTE:* This bug report is for *JIRA Server*. Using *JIRA Cloud*? [See the corresponding bug report|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JRACLOUD-24113].
  {panel}

This was not seen in the upgrade from 4.2.x to 4.3-rc1 on JAC

This affects a change between 4.3-rc1 and 4.3 where if a customer has a full path in log4j.properties

We could have a customer customising their log4j with this example:
{code}
log4j.appender.filelog.File=/opt/j2ee/domains/atlassian.com/qa-jac/jira-home/log/atlassian-jira.log

{code}

What happens with this setting is that the log file will go to a double path:

*Result:*
{code}
/opt/j2ee/domains/atlassian.com/qa-jac/jira-home/log/opt/j2ee/domains/atlassian.com/qa-jac/jira-home/log/atlassian-jira.log
{code}
*Expected:*
{code}
/opt/j2ee/domains/atlassian.com/qa-jac/jira-home/log/atlassian-jira.log
{code}


In 4.3 we changed it go be this by default:
{code}
log4j.appender.filelog.File=atlassian-jira.log
{code}

