At present Jira will hide a given transition link if a condition for that transition is not met.
The problem is that unless the end user is fully aware of the details of the workflow, it's not immediately apparent why the transition is not available, even if the condition issue is something that they have the necessary permissions to resolve.

It would be great if Jira would present some form of indication beside the Workflow buttons along the lines of "Missing Transitions" which when clicked, would present a hover dialog listing the transitions that are missing and the conditions that must be met for each transition to become available

